## Quick Start Example

```bash
# 1. Generate lab for Day 01 (auto-detects type)
/create-lab --day=01

# Output:
# Stage 0: Auto-Detect Lab Type
#   Primary Type:   CFD
#   Confidence:     69%
#   Scores: CFD=84%, C++=15%
#   → Creating CFD lab...

# 2. Follow the prompts for each stage
# Stage 0: Auto-detect type (script analyzes content)
# Stage 1: Extract ground truth (Claude does this)
# Stage 2: Generate skeleton (Claude does this)
# Stage 3: Verify (DeepSeek R1 verifies)
# Stage 4: Generate content (DeepSeek Chat V3 writes lab)
# Stage 5: QC (script validates)

# 3. Review the generated lab
cat daily_learning/Phase_01_Foundation_Theory/01_lab.md

# 4. Test the lab yourself
cd $FOAM_RUN
mkdir -p lab01
cd lab01
# Follow lab steps...
```

